om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">ESG HR</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">We talked a few weeks ago about the do=
cumentary-filmmaker son of a financial-services billionaire who hated worki=
ng in financial services and loves alternative medicine=C2=A0and =E2=80=9Ca=
rchetypal astrology.=E2=80=9D He now works as the head of environmental, so=
cial and governance affairs at his dad=E2=80=99s firm, Interactive Brokers =
Group Inc. <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/2710090=
2.294602/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMD=
MtMDIvcnVzc2lhLXMtZmluYW5jZXMtYXJlLWNsb3NpbmctdXA_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDMyMTIyX01PT=
kVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09=
MjIwMzIxJnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBd11286f0"=
 itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"=
color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px;=
 border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color=
: #ccc;"> I wrote</a>:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Imagine =
being the=C2=A0<em>deputy=C2=A0</em>director of ESG at Interactive Brokers.=
 Presumably you got hired based on your background doing ESG initiatives at=
 major financial firms.=C2=A0Presumably you think of ESG as a real career p=
ath in finance, and you have spent your career building expertise in the th=
eory and practice and complex accounting of ESG.=C2=A0But you=E2=80=99ve go=
t to compete with financial-services heirs, and=C2=A0<a href=3D"https://lin=
k.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/27100902.294602/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cubnl0aW1l=
cy5jb20vMjAyMS8xMC8xMi9idXNpbmVzcy9kZWFsYm9vay9oYXJyeS1tZWdoYW4tZXRoaWNhbC1=
pbnZlc3RvcnMuaHRtbA/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB20cbc95e" target=3D"_blank" st=
yle=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-widt=
h: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; backgroun=
d-color: #ccc;">British-monarchy heirs</a>=C2=A0for that matter. ESG is, so=
mewhat paradoxically, an attractive area of finance for people who don=E2=
=80=99t care about finance but do like the money it provides.</p></blockquo=
te><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Broadly speaking you might expect there to =
be a=C2=A0lot of those people. Not so much ESG heirs, maybe,=C2=A0but peopl=
e who don=E2=80=99t care much about finance and nonetheless want a job in f=
inancial services. You might assume that there are a lot of people who go t=
o fancy colleges and have a vague desire to make the world a better place. =
As they approach graduation, they go to the career-services office and say =
=E2=80=9Chow can I save the world?=E2=80=9D Career services says: =E2=80=9C=
Well, you can go work at a nonprofit for a low salary, or you can go do env=
ironmental reporting=C2=A0at a big asset manager for a high salary.=E2=80=
=9D (Or, they go to their parents, who work in finance, and say =E2=80=9CI =
am going to save the world by working at a nonprofit,=E2=80=9D and the pare=
nts say =E2=80=9Cwell let=E2=80=99s not be too hasty, have you considered E=
SG investing? I could hook you up.=E2=80=9D) And so there is a steady suppl=
y of people who don=E2=80=99t care about finance but who end up working in =
financial services=C2=A0in ESG roles.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">If th=
is is your model, you might expect:</p><ol style=3D"list-style-type: decima=
l; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;">=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;=
">The ESG people will get paid=C2=A0less than the regular finance people at=
 their firms, because there is a glut of them and their alternative is work=
ing at nonprofits for much less money; and=C2=A0</li>=09<li style=3D"margin=
-bottom: 5px;">There will be a certain amount of bad blood and suspicion be=
tween the ESG people (who hate finance and want to save the world) and the =
regular finance people (who like finance and, uh, sometimes get stereotyped=
 as not caring so much about the world?).</li></ol><p style=3D"margin: 16px=
 0;">Here is a funny=C2=A0<a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.co=
m/click/27100902.294602/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuZnQuY29tL2NvbnRlbnQvZmU1ODUzYTQtYmE=
zZS00MzRhLWFiZTAtMWI0M2MwOTRhZTg1/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB831c9e32" itempr=
op=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: =
#000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border=
-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;=
">Financial Times article</a> about the booming market for ESG specialists,=
 which suggests that that model is basically correct, but that=C2=A0it is c=
hanging as ESG investing becomes hugely popular and it is hard to fill role=
s:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In a CFA Institute analysis =
of 10,000 investment jobs advertised on LinkedIn, 6 per cent required susta=
inability skills, yet less than 1 per cent of the 1m investment professiona=
l profiles included in the study listed these skills on their profiles. ...=
</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">As a consequence, pay gaps between ESG sta=
ff and other investment roles are closing fast. =E2=80=9C[Hiring] used to b=
e cheaper because sustainability was popular and everyone wanted to do it,=
=E2=80=9D Ferguson said.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Candidates are oft=
en fielding multiple offers that can be significantly above their current s=
alary. Ruck Keene said that for recruiters: =E2=80=9CIt=E2=80=99s quite dif=
ficult to get people over the line. Nobody wants to lose their ESG speciali=
st. We=E2=80=99re seeing compensation increases of 30 to 50 per cent.=E2=80=
=9D =E2=80=A6</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Education is another key fact=
or. Though the CFA Institute started offering a certificate in ESG investin=
g last year, few business schools currently have programmes that offer both=
 financial and sustainability training to the same level. It=E2=80=99s stil=
l =E2=80=9Cpretty church and state=E2=80=9D, said Robert Eccles, an expert =
on sustainability reporting and strategies at the University of Oxford. =E2=
=80=9CFinance people think it=E2=80=99s all BS, sustainability people don=
=E2=80=99t know finance.=E2=80=9D</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px =
0;">I think that one way to understand the proliferation of ESG reporting r=
egimes, carbon credit trading systems, etc., is that adding a lot of rules =
and complexity to ESG=C2=A0<em>makes it feel more like finance</em>. Lots o=
f people in financial services are not all that interested in, say, tax pol=
icy, but if you give them 1,000 pages of tax regulations they will be like =
=E2=80=9Coh goody let=E2=80=99s find some trades!=E2=80=9D</p><p style=3D"m=
argin: 16px 0;">Or you could think of the 2008 financial crisis as being dr=
iven, to some extent, by people asking themselves =E2=80=9Cwhat is the risk=
iest possible thing that I could construct that will nonetheless get a AAA =
rating from the credit ratings agencies?=E2=80=9D =E2=80=9CBuy things that =
yield a lot but are safe=E2=80=9D is a reasonable, dull mandate for an inve=
stment manager, but =E2=80=9Cunderstand the ratings agency criteria for str=
uctured credit inside and out so that you can maximize yield subject to the=
 constraint of achieving a AAA rating=E2=80=9D is a <em>fun puzzle</em>.</p=
><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Similarly, if you take a stereotypical=C2=A0h=
edge fund manager and tell her =E2=80=9Ctry to make money but also do good =
with your investments,=E2=80=9D she will find that first mandate clear and =
exciting, and the second one vague and open-ended. But if you tell her =E2=
=80=9Ctry to make money and here is a thicket of regulations about ESG repo=
rting,=E2=80=9D she will say =E2=80=9Coh goody let=E2=80=99s find an arbitr=
age!=E2=80=9D What is the <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.co=
m/click/27100902.294602/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGl=
jbGVzLzIwMjEtMDktMDkvdHdlbnR5LXBlcmNlbnQtb2YtYS1waWN0dXJlLW9mLWEtZG9nP2NtcG=
lkPUJCRDAzMjEyMl9NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzb=
GV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIyMDMyMSZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8=
524a319a23cB3a9719ad" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=
=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; bord=
er-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: so=
lid; background-color: #ccc;"> most complicated way</a> to own oil companie=
s and have a zero-carbon portfolio? If there are complex regulations to opt=
imize, it just feels like a real finance job in a way that =E2=80=9Cmake th=
e world better=E2=80=9D does not.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"><a href=
=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/27100902.294602/aHR0cHM6L=
y93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMDMtMjEvc2VjLXRvLXJlcXVp=
cmUtY29tcGFuaWVzLXRvLWRpc2Nsb3NlLXBvbGx1dGlvbi11bmRlci1uZXctcGxhbj9jbXBpZD1=
CQkQwMzIxMjJfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldH=
RlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yMjAzMjEmdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a=
319a23cB38c5dab6" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"=
_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-b=
ottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid;=
 background-color: #ccc;"> Elsewhere</a>:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin=
: 16px 0;">Companies will need to reveal detailed information about their g=
reenhouse gas pollution under a new U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission=
 plan, marking a major shift in how corporations must show they are dealing=
 with climate change.=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">For the first t=
ime ever, the agency plans to require businesses to outline the risks a war=
ming planet poses to their operations when they file registration statement=
s, annual reports or other documents. Some large companies will have to pro=
vide information on emissions they don=E2=80=99t make themselves, but come =
from other firms in their supply chain. =E2=80=A6</p><p style=3D"margin: 16=
px 0;">=E2=80=9COver the generations, the SEC has stepped in when there=E2=
=80=99s significant need for the disclosure of information relevant to inve=
stors=E2=80=99 decisions,=E2=80=9D SEC Chair Gary Gensler said in a stateme=
nt. =E2=80=9CToday=E2=80=99s proposal would help issuers more efficiently a=
nd effectively disclose these risks.=E2=80=9D</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0=
;">The SEC would also require auditors or other experts to review the clima=
te disclosures, which would be phased-in over time.</p><p style=3D"margin: =
16px 0;">Climate activists will likely cheer the agency=E2=80=99s decision =
to require larger companies to disclose some of their so-called Scope 3 emi=
ssions, which are generated by other firms in their supply chain or custome=
rs using their products. That information, which business groups say is ver=
y hard to quantify, wouldn=E2=80=99t be subject to an audit.</p></blockquot=
e><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Man is that going to create a lot of ESG job=
s.</p><table class=3D"liveintent-sponsored-content" width=3D"auto" cellpadd=
